      SUBROUTINE BORT2(STR1,STR2)

!$$$  SUBPROGRAM DOCUMENTATION BLOCK
!
! SUBPROGRAM:    BORT2
!   PRGMMR: KEYSER           ORG: NP22       DATE: 2003-11-04
!
! ABSTRACT: THIS SUBROUTINE PRINTS (TO STDOUT) TWO GIVEN ERROR STRINGS
!   AND THEN CALLS BUFR ARCHIVE LIBRARY SUBROUTINE BORT_EXIT TO ABORT
!   THE APPLICATION PROGRAM CALLING THE BUFR ARCHIVE LIBRARY SOFTWARE.
!   IT IS SIMILAR TO BUFR ARCHIVE LIBRARY SUBROUTINE BORT, EXCEPT BORT
!   PRINTS ONLY ONE ERROR STRING.
!
! PROGRAM HISTORY LOG:
! 2003-11-04  D. KEYSER  -- ORIGINAL AUTHOR
!
! USAGE:    CALL BORT2 (STR1, STR2)
!   INPUT ARGUMENT LIST:
!     STR1     - CHARACTER*(*): FIRST ERROR MESSAGE TO BE PRINTED TO
!                STANDARD OUTPUT
!     STR2     - CHARACTER*(*): SECOND ERROR MESSAGE TO BE PRINTED TO
!                STANDARD OUTPUT
!
!   OUTPUT FILES:
!     UNIT 06  - STANDARD OUTPUT PRINT
!
! REMARKS:
!    THIS ROUTINE CALLS:        BORT_EXIT
!    THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED BY: ELEMDX   GETNTBE  PARSEQ   PARSTR
!                               PARUSR   PARUTG   RDUSDX   SEQSDX
!                               SNTBBE   SNTBDE   STRING   UFBINT
!                               UFBOVR   UFBREP   UFBSTP   VALX
!                               Normally not called by any application
!                               programs but it could be.
!
! ATTRIBUTES:
!   LANGUAGE: FORTRAN 77
!   MACHINE:  PORTABLE TO ALL PLATFORMS
!
!$$$

      CHARACTER*(*) STR1, STR2
      PRINT*
      PRINT*,'**************BUFR ARCHIVE LIBRARY ABORT*****************'
      PRINT*,STR1
      PRINT*,STR2
      PRINT*,'**************BUFR ARCHIVE LIBRARY ABORT*****************'
      PRINT*
      CALL BORT_EXIT
      END SUBROUTINE BORT2
